cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.FL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper deals with testing software systems. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses functional equivalence classes of the software under test. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper formalizes the problem of testing nondeterministic systems as a game played on a finite game graph. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses techniques for testing nondeterministic systems. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper uses formal methods to analyze the complexity of the problem of finding the maximal number of nodes that the tester can guarantee to visit.
